00:37:00.090 --> 00:37:03.000
So we take that distance.

00:37:03.000 --> 00:37:06.360
And then we want to think
about how fast that would then

00:37:06.360 --> 00:37:10.110
go to 0.

00:37:10.110 --> 00:37:15.510
And it's fast, approximately
10 to the 10th seconds.

00:37:15.510 --> 00:37:19.190
Or the electron should
plummet into the nucleus

00:37:19.190 --> 00:37:20.946
in about 0.1 nanoseconds.

00:37:24.280 --> 00:37:26.426
It doesn't do that though.

00:37:26.426 --> 00:37:29.000
So we have these
beautiful classical laws.

00:37:29.000 --> 00:37:31.360
I'm a big fan of f equals Ma.

00:37:31.360 --> 00:37:33.210
I like all these things.

00:37:33.210 --> 00:37:36.450
But it's not working to
describe what's happening here.

00:37:36.450 --> 00:37:39.050
So we discovered the electron,
discovered the nucleus,

00:37:39.050 --> 00:37:40.410
but now we have a new problem.

00:37:40.410 --> 00:37:43.550
We don't understand
why the electron isn't

00:37:43.550 --> 00:37:45.920
plummeting into the nucleus.

00:37:45.920 --> 00:37:49.160
So what's the problem here?

00:37:49.160 --> 00:37:56.530
So is the problem Coulomb's
Force or Newton's Second Law?

00:37:56.530 --> 00:38:00.280
And it turns out, as most
of you are probably aware,

00:38:00.280 --> 00:38:04.100
it's that classical mechanics
doesn't work when you consider

00:38:04.100 --> 00:38:06.320
things on this size scale.

00:38:06.320 --> 00:38:11.750
So we need a new way to
describe what's going on here.

00:38:11.750 --> 00:38:14.550
Classical mechanics
isn't working.

00:38:14.550 --> 00:38:17.990
And so we need
quantum mechanics.

00:38:17.990 --> 00:38:21.860
And so that is allowing us
to understand the behavior

00:38:21.860 --> 00:38:23.530
that we're actually observing.

00:38:23.530 --> 00:38:25.460
We're not observing
this plummeting,

00:38:25.460 --> 00:38:27.650
so there must be a
better way to do this.

00:38:27.650 --> 00:38:30.380
And when you're on this
really small scale,

00:38:30.380 --> 00:38:33.110
you need a different way
to describe the behavior.

